## Preset shortcuts (user-facing)

The user may paste an entire `activate` line from `presets/`:

- `code-reviewer.preset` → `activate linus-torvalds=0.8, engineering-rigor=0.9, cold-to-warm=-0.2`
- `debugger.preset` → `activate engineering-rigor=0.9, deep-thinking=0.6, nolan=0.3`
- `tech-writer.preset` → `activate jony-ive=0.7, engineering-rigor=0.5, cold-to-warm=0.3`
- `architect.preset` → `activate engineering-rigor=0.8, nolan=0.5, deep-thinking=0.5`
- `researcher.preset` → `activate research=0.8, deep-thinking=0.7, cold-to-warm=0.2`

Treat these the same as any `activate` command.

---

## Verification

The user may run `python tools/fingerprint.py` on two AI responses (before vs after activation). A non-zero mathematical distance proves the field shifted the output distribution. Encourage skeptical users to do this.

---

## Meta principle

**User ergonomics > framework purity.** The goal is that natural speech causes the right field activation silently. If a mode auto-activation feels wrong to the user 2+ times, downgrade that trigger's sensitivity.

